{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The primary translator produces a grammatically coherent translation that preserves the meaning of the source text, not just a word-for-word substitution.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — mocked outputs cannot reveal real model quality failures. REAL-INFRA: depends on real translation API behavior. MOCK-HIDE: yes — fixed mocks can always look coherent. LLM-DEP: yes — correctness depends on model output quality and variability. MULTI-STEP: no, this is a single agentic step.","test_description":"Call the real neural translation API with a curated multilingual set (idioms, tense, agreement, ambiguous phrases) and assert semantic-adequacy/fluency thresholds against human-labeled references or a robust semantic scoring rubric; fail if output is literal-but-wrong or ungrammatical.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the translation API returns a 503 error, the service transparently falls back to the dictionary-based translator without returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — in-process mocks can miss real HTTP/status handling and client retry/error mapping issues. REAL-INFRA: yes — requires real HTTP error path. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocked client exceptions may not match actual 503 response semantics. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Run the service against a real HTTP stub server that returns 503 for translation requests; verify caller receives a successful fallback translation response, not an error, and confirm fallback path was exercised.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.6,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The dictionary-based fallback returns the correct pre-stored translation for phrases that exist in the SQLite database.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — mocking repository access can miss SQL/query/schema/encoding issues. REAL-INFRA: local SQLite I/O is needed, but no OS/process/network boundary beyond local DB. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocked DAO would always return expected value. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Seed a real SQLite test DB with phrase/translation rows, invoke fallback translator through service data-access layer, and assert exact returned translation for known phrases (including Unicode/diacritics cases).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The quality tracking comparison correctly computes edit distance between primary and fallback outputs and stores the metric.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — pure unit tests of distance math miss persistence wiring/type/schema failures. REAL-INFRA: needs local DB write/read verification, not external system. MOCK-HIDE: yes — mocked storage can hide serialization or column-mapping bugs. LLM-DEP: no (use deterministic strings). MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Use deterministic primary/fallback string pairs with known character edit distances, run quality-tracking path end-to-end through metric computation plus SQLite persistence, then read back stored values and verify exact distances.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators are available, the service returns the primary translation and logs the quality comparison in the background.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — in-process mocks can miss real async/background execution timing and HTTP/client behavior. REAL-INFRA: yes — real HTTP call plus background task execution boundary. MOCK-HIDE: yes — synchronous mocks may falsely pass while production drops background logging. LLM-DEP: no (selection logic, not output quality). MULTI-STEP: not agentic multi-step.","test_description":"Run service with a real HTTP translator endpoint (healthy response) and real SQLite; issue request and assert immediate response uses primary translation, then asynchronously verify quality metric record appears within timeout without blocking request latency.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.27,"System":0.6,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.05}}]}
